Nested dynamic routes in Nextjs are routes where:

1. We have multiple dynamic segments .
2. Those segments are inside each other(nested folder).
3. Each segment can represent hierarchical data(user --> post --> comment) . 

What is a Nested Dynamic Routes?

A Dynamic folder inside another dynamic folder.

         /user/43/posts/100 
                |       |
                |       | 
    Dynamic UserID    Dynamic PostID  


Limitations of Dynamic Nested Routes 

In Next.js dynamic nested routes are defined using square brcackets, such as [userid] or[postId] , allowing for Urls like /users/42/posts/100 

But we need 
1. Fixed Depth
2. Rigid Structure

so nextjs have catch all segments 
